<p class="no-box"><b>This will be updated frequently.</b><br>


<h3>Week One</h3><p class="no-box">March 31- April 5.
<ul>
<li><b>Class 1</b>:  Introduction to the course.  Introductory discussion of
  energy, conservation of energy, and power. 
<li><b>Lab 1</b>:  Measurement and watt meters.  
  <!--Before lab sign up for a
  google account if you don't already have one.  You'll need this to
  use google docs. We'll be using google spreadsheets throughout the
  class.--> 
<li><b>Class 2</b>: Read Chapter 1 of SEWTHA.  Bring to class a few
  benchmarks about population and greenhouse gas emissions.  Energy
  vs. power.  
</ul>
<br>


<h3>Week Two</h3><p class="no-box">April 7-11
<ul>
<li><b>Class 3</b>: Different types of energy.  Electric current.
  Generating electricity.  
<li><b>Lab 2</b>: Build your own electric generator.
<li><b>Class 4</b>: The power grid. 
</ul>
<br>


<h3>Week Three</h3><p class="no-box">April 14-18
<ul>
<li><b>Class 5</b>: Thermal energy.
<li><b>Lab 3</b>: Discussion of project topics
<li><b>Class 6</b>: Thermal energy.  Begin finance: time value of money.
</ul>
<br>



